properties.name: -fx-region-background
properties.description:
Values: javafx.scene.layout.Background

Default: null

Comments: This cannot be set directly from CSS but is created from the property values of -fx-background-color, -fx-background-image, -fx-background-insets, -fx-background-position, -fx-background-radius, -fx-background-repeat, -fx-background-size

properties.name: -fx-background-color
properties.description:
Values: <paint> [ , <paint> ]*

Default: transparent

Comments: A series of paint values separated by commas.

properties.name: -fx-background-insets
properties.description:
Values: <size> | <size> <size> <size> <size> [ , [ <size> | <size> <size> <size> <size>] ]*

Default: 0 0 0 0

Comments: A series of size values or sets of four size values, separated by commas. A single size value means all insets are the same. Otherwise, the four values for each inset are given in the order top, right, bottom, left. Each comma-separated value or set of values in the series applies to the corresponding background color.

properties.name: -fx-background-radius
properties.description:
Values: [<size>]{1,4} [ / [<size>]{1,4} ]? [ , [<size>]{1,4} [ / [<size>]{1,4} ]? ]*

Default: 0 0 0 0

Comments: The same syntax and semenatics as CSS Backgrounds and Borders Module Level 3: Curve Radii applies to -fx-background-radius. Note that JavaFX supports only the short-hand syntax. Each comma-separated value or set of values in the series applies to the corresponding background color.

properties.name: -fx-background-image
properties.description:
Values: <uri> [ , <uri> ]*

Default: null

Comments: A series of image URIs separated by commas.

properties.name: -fx-background-position
properties.description:
Values: <bg-position> [ , <bg-position> ]* where <bg-position> = [     [ [ <size> | left | center | right ] [ <size> | top | center | bottom ]? ]     | [ [ center | [ left | right ] <size>? ] || [ center | [ top | bottom ] <size>? ] ]

Default: 0% 0%

Comments: A series of <bg-position> values separated by commas. Each bg-position item in the series applies to the corresponding image in the background-image series.

properties.name: -fx-background-repeat
-fx-background-size
properties.description:
Values: <bg-size> [ , <bg-size> ]* <bg-size> = [ <size> | auto ]{1,2} | cover | contain | stretch

Default: auto auto

Comments: A series of <bg-size> values separated by commas. Each bg-size item in the series applies to the corresponding image in the background-image series.

properties.name: -fx-region-border
properties.description:
Values: javafx.scene.layout.Border

Default: null

Comments: This cannot be set directly from CSS but is created from the property values of -fx-border-color, -fx-border-insets, -fx-border-radius,  -fx-border-style, -fx-border-width, -fx-border-image-insets, -fx-border-image-repeat, -fx-border-image-slice, -fx-border-image-source, -fx-border-image-width

properties.name: -fx-border-color
properties.description:
Values: <paint> | <paint> <paint> <paint> <paint> [ , [<paint> | <paint> <paint> <paint> <paint>] ]*

Default: null

Comments: A series of paint values or sets of four paint values, separated by commas. For each item in the series, if a single paint value is specified, then that paint is used as the border for all sides of the region; and if a set of four paints is specified, they are used for the top, right, bottom, and left borders of the region, in that order. If the border is not rectangular, only the first paint value in the set is used.

properties.name: -fx-border-insets
properties.description:
Values: <size> | <size> <size> <size> <size> [ , [ <size> | <size> <size> <size> <size>] ]*

Default: null

Comments: A series of inset or sets of four inset values, separated by commas. For each item in the series, a single inset value means that all insets are the same; and if a set of four inset values is specified, they are used for the top, right, bottom, and left edges of the region, in that order. Each item in the series of insets applies to the corresponding item in the series of border colors.

properties.name: -fx-border-radius
properties.description:
Values: [<size>]{1,4} [ / [<size>]{1,4} ]? [ , [<size>]{1,4} [ / [<size>]{1,4} ]? ]*

Default: null

Comments: Refer to CSS Backgrounds and Borders Module Level 3: Curve Radii. JavaFX supports only the short-hand syntax. Each comma-separated value or set of values in the series applies to the corresponding border color.

properties.name: -fx-border-style
properties.description:
Values: <border-style> [ , <border-style> ]* where <border-style> = <dash-style> [phase <number>]? [centered | inside | outside]? [line-join [miter <number> | bevel | round]]? [line-cap [square | butt | round]]? where <dash-style> = [ none | solid | dotted | dashed | segments( <number>, <number> [, <number>]*) ]

Default: null

Comments: A series of border style values, separated by commas. Each item in the series applies to the corresponding item in the series of border colors. The segments dash-style defines a sequence representing the lengths of the dash segments. Alternate entries in the sequence represent the lengths of the opaque and transparent segments of the dashes. This corresponds to the strokeDashArray variable of Shape. The optional phase parameter defines the point in the dashing pattern that will correspond to the beginning of the stroke. This corresponds to the strokeDashOffset variable of Shape.

properties.name: -fx-border-width
properties.description:
Values: <size> | <size> <size> <size> <size> [ , [ <size> | <size> <size> <size> <size>] ]*

Default: null

Comments: A series of width or sets of four width values, separated by commas. For each item in the series, a single width value means that all border widths are the same; and if a set of four width values is specified, they are used for the top, right, bottom, and left border widths, in that order. If the border is not rectangular, only the first width value is used. Each item in the series of widths applies to the corresponding item in the series of border colors.

properties.name: -fx-border-image-source
properties.description:
Values: <uri> [ , <uri> ]*

Default: null

Comments: A series of image URIs, separated by commas.

properties.name: -fx-border-image-insets
properties.description:
Values: <size> | <size> <size> <size> <size> [ , [ <size> | <size> <size> <size> <size>] ]*

Default: 0 0 0 0

Comments: A series of inset or sets of four inset values, separated by commas. For each item in the series, a single inset value means that all insets are the same; and if a set of four inset values is specified, they are used for the top, right, bottom, and left edges of the region, in that order. Each item in the series of insets applies to the corresponding image in the series of border images.

properties.name: -fx-border-image-repeat
-fx-border-image-slice
properties.description:
Values: [<size> | <size> <size> <size> <size> ] fill? [ , [ <size> | <size> <size> <size> <size> <size> ] fill? ]*

Default: 100%

Comments: A series of image slice values or sets of four values, separated by commas. Each item in the series applies to the corresponding image in the series of border images. For each item in the series, if four values are given, they specify the size of the top, right, bottom, and left slices. This effectively divides the image into nine regions: an upper left corner, a top edge, an upper right corner, a right edge, a lower right corner, a bottom edge, a lower left corner, a left edge and a middle. If one value is specified, this value is used for the slice values for all four edges. If 'fill' is present, the middle slice is preserved, otherwise it is discarded. Percentage values may be used here, in which case the values are considered proportional to the source image.

properties.name: -fx-border-image-width
properties.description:
Values: <size> | <size> <size> <size> <size> [ , [ <size> | <size> <size> <size> <size>] ]*

Default: 1 1 1 1

Comments: A series of width or sets of four width values, separated by commas. For each item in the series, a single width value means that all border widths are the same; and if a set of four width values is specified, they are used for the top, right, bottom, and left border widths, in that order. If the border is not rectangular, only the first width value is used. Each item in the series of widths applies to the corresponding item in the series of border images. Percentage values may be used here, in which case the values are considered proportional to the border image area.

properties.name: -fx-padding
properties.description:
Values: <size> | <size> <size> <size> <size>

Default: 0 0 0 0

Comments: A sets of four padding values, separated by commas. For each item in the series, a single padding value means that all padding are the same; and if a set of four padding values is specified, they are used for the top, right, bottom, and left edges of the region, in that order.

properties.name: -fx-position-shape
properties.description:
Values: <boolean>

Default: true

Comments: If true means the shape centered within the region's width and height, otherwise the shape is positioned at its source position. Has no effect if a shape string is not specified.

properties.name: -fx-scale-shape
properties.description:
Values: <boolean>

Default: true

Comments: If true means the shape is scaled to fit the size of the region, otherwise the shape is at its source size, and its position depends on the value of the position-shape property. Has no effect if a shape string is not specified.

properties.name: -fx-shape
properties.description:
Values: "<string>"

Default: null

Comments: An SVG path string. By specifying a shape here the region takes on that shape instead of a rectangle or rounded rectangle. The syntax of this path string is specified in [3].

properties.name: -fx-snap-to-pixel
properties.description:
Values: <boolean>

Default: true

Comments: Defines whether this region rounds position/spacing and ceils size values to pixel boundaries when laying out its children.

properties.name: -fx-region-background
properties.description:
Values: 

Default: null

Comments: This property is set by specifying -fx-background-color and/or -fx-background-image. Optionally, the properties -fx-background-insets, -fx-background-radius, -fx-background-position, -fx-background-repeat, and -fx-background-size may also be set. In order to set the Region background to null, specify the style "-fx-background-color: null; -fx-background-image: null;". There is no shorthand notation for -fx-region-background at this time.

properties.name: -fx-region-border
properties.description:

In order to set the Region background to null, specify the style "-fx-border-color: null; -fx-border-image: null;". There is no shorthand notation for -fx-region-border at this time.
